		"description": "<p>Even if you don’t know a creature’s language, if you can listen to their speech (or engage with their communicatory means, if it’s not a speech-based language) for one hour you can make out enough of their language to understand simple meaning. You can’t grasp elaborate ideas, but you can get the gist of what they’re saying. Your own communication is much more limited-basically “yes” and “no”, adjusted for tone.</p>",
